SUMMARY:Acadia Nat’l Park/Partial Solar Eclipse/Perseids Meteor Shower Event
DESCRIPTION:Triangle Hiking and Outdoors Group\nCome and be a part of one of THOG’s most ambitious trips. This summer adventure in Maine includes Acadia National Park and Bar Harbor\, as well as two amazing celestial events- A partial Solar Eclipse and the Perseids Meteor Shower.\nThis exciting road trip event will be slightly different from other THOG events. We will be partnering with Wanderful Journeys\, a local travel club that hosts trips to various destinations. I decided to team up with them so it would provide us with another layer of resources for planning\, as well as to enhance the trip experience.\n**See RSVP requirements below before you register**.\n\n**Highlights of our weeklong trip will include:**\n-Hikes in Acadia National Park such as Precipice Trail and Beehive Trail\n-Thunder Hole\n-Jordan Pond\n-Maine Lobster :)\n-Lighthouses in Maine\n-Viewing the partial Solar Eclipse\n-Watching the Perseids Meteor Shower (up to 100 per hour)\n-Exploring Bar Harbor\n-Bar Island Trail hike- a trail that appears only during low tide\n-Exclusive Swag options for trip participants\n\n**Here is a brief overview of our itinerary on this trip** which is subject to change depending on weather and/or other factors:\n8/9- Carpools will meet in a central location in the triangle and begin Day 1 of our trip with an overnight stop at a hotel in NJ\n8/10- Continue our trip with a featured stop along the way at Portland Head Light then arrive at Acadia Nat'l Park/Bar Harbor for either camping or hotel stay\n8/11- Sunrise at Cadillac Mountain\, hiking choices in Acadia and other activities then dinner at camp or in Bar Harbor\n8/12- Solar Eclipse Day Activities: Sunrise and hike at Otter Point\, Watch partial Solar Eclipse nearby\, Explore Bar Harbor\, Sunset at Bass Harbor Head Lighthouse\n8/13- Activities: Bar Island Trail hike\, Thunder Hole\, Jordan Pond\n8/14- Head back to NJ to our hotel with a featured stop along the way.\n8/15- Continue our trip back home with a featured stop along the way.\nAll participants will be required to pay a $100 deposit to secure their spot on this trip.\n**Accommodations overview:** Everyone will be staying at a designated hotel in NJ going to Maine and returning from Maine.\nIn Maine\, you will have two stay options:\n-designated Group Campsites (4 nights) that has modern bathrooms\; paid showers are located nearby\n-designated hotel in Bar Harbor (4 nights) two beds per room\nIf you choose the hotel stay in Maine\, it is crucial that you submit your deposit as soon as you RSVP (see rsvp requirements below) to secure your hotel spot due to limited room availability. Roommate info/rules will also be in a link that will be sent to all who RSVP.\n**important RSVP requirements:**\n\n1. You will be asked a three-part question as you are RSVPing for this event. Please answer completely!\n2. After you RSVP to this trip\, you will be sent a **link to your email** **address** that will have questions you need to answer as well as a link to pay your **$100 deposit (required for every trip participant)**. Links will have all the information about the trip\, total costs per person\, rules on how the deposit works\, itinerary\, trip expectations\, and swag information.\nYour spot on this trip will not be guaranteed until the deposit is paid.\n\nWe look forward to having you be a part of this adventure!\nIf you have any questions\, please send me (Larredo) a meetup message or comment below if it is something that could benefit the group. Thanks!\nSee you all soon!\nLarredo and Geniece\n\nTRIP PARTICIPANT WAIVER OF LIABILITY I fully realize that this activity involves a risk of personal injury\, property damage\, or loss of my person or property. I hereby for myself\, my heirs\, executors and administrators\, and same for persons with whom are in my party\, waive and release any claims or rights against Triangle Hiking & Outdoors Group (THOG)\, all of its owners and coordinators for any and all injury\, damages or loss to my person or property incurred during this activity. I also understand that THOG organizers are not required\, nor should it be assumed that they are CPR/First Aid/Wilderness Survival Certified and I am responsible for my own personal safety.
